dating.remarks: Dye zaigung des hochlobwirdigen hailigthums der stifftkirchen aller hailigen zu Wittenburg (The display of the highly praised reliquaries of the church of All Saints at Wittenberg)

pageContext.description:
Title page with electoral coat of arms (recto) and an image of All Saints Church (verso) in: 'Dye zaigung des hochlobwirdigen hailigthums der stifftkirchen aller hailigen zu Wittenburg' (The display of the highly praised reliquaries of the church of All Saints at Wittenberg) A set of 108 woodcuts by Lucas Cranach the Elder, showing reliquaries and treasures in the church of All Saints in Wittenberg, with letterpress throughout. First edition printed by Symphorian Reinhart, Wittenberg, 1509.
Also used in the second edition of 'Dye zaigung des hochlobwirdigen hailigthums der Stifft kirchen aller hailigen zu wittenberg', Symphorian Reinhart, Wittenberg 1510  [VD16 Z 250] near the end of the book with an impression of the risen Christ on the reverse.
Frequently found on the reverse of small format painted portrait series of Friedrich III. the Wise from 1532
